channel.title: RSPS hacking - how to find bank interface for bank5 packet?
channel.description: If I want to open up bank I can use for example 5292 and one server uses 23000 which has also bankall option. However when I try to use bank5 packet (its packet that is used for depositing/withdrawing/buying/selling) those interfaces won't work. How can I find what interface my client uses to withdraw items from bank?

Both of you are wrong, I tested this packet with shop interface and I can buy with it. Since its same packet it does owrk. However when I tested default bank interfaces like 5292 and so on they do NOT work. Interface is somehow different, its propably only used in withdrawing items from bank.
[/quote]I regret attempting to help you. What’s the point of posting a question if you’re going to completely ignore a solution that provided the answer to exactly what you asked for.

item.title: RSPS hacking - how to find bank interface for bank5 packet?
item.dc:creator: @Lin Lin
item.description:
@Lin wrote:

Usually if they don’t work, there’s a problem with how you’re reading the data. An example of this is something like using readWord instead of readWordA, so the value appears 128 lower than it should (or higher, I forget). What you can do is make your server print out the values of the interface when you go to bank, so like System.out.println("Bank " + interfaceID); and you’ll get the proper ID to use.
